reviews.text: We take the kids almost every year. We like to have picnics there. Fun to feed the ducks by hand. Plenty of room for the kids to run and play. They have several playgrounds.  Clean restrooms. Snack bar is a bit pricey. Nice paved walking paths around the pond. Would make awesome photo shoots during fall/Autumn.
Great place for a walk! Grew up with this Park,lived and went to school nearby as a child. Later bought a home near the park. Have long since moved but still make time to come back.
We love the ducks and swans. Both my boys can't wait until the museum is open. Very fun trip, also great history lesson posted.
They have two great playgrounds and a lovely lake to walk around. Be careful of the duck droppings. :)

This park is actually a pretty lovely place to walk through during the Spring and Summer. This time of year there's not a whole lot going on, but the trails to walk through the park are still accessible. The lake is a wonder itself with all the large carp, and variety of water foul that inhabit in it.

I'm excited for the new place! I always enjoy it. The variety of shows offered is awesome. A great place to take a date, see a play, the symphony, ballet. A great gem and an anchor to Hagerstown culture. I'm so grateful to have The Maryland Theatre here!

Although it us under construction.  The staff and shows are always wonderful.  I love getting out and enjoying something local that is special.  It has a nostalgic feel.  I can't wait to see the renovations.
There is a website that rips people off, sells $15 tickets for over $50 BEWARE!!! But tickets directly from the theater.

There was a slight change in the seating as I had I ordered balcony both x seats on Ticketmaster only to find I got lower level Orchestra Box seats.  The theater staff were very kind and pleasant in correcting the issue, and the lower Orchestra Box seats actually were much better than the original seats I purchased.  Amy Grant is an outstanding performer, and I highly recommend anyone to see her in a theater style venue for the higher quality sound!!  Love the show!!!
Beautiful theater with lots of concerts and plays. Going through a renovation that is going to make it even better.

I have always been proud of the beautiful Theater's preservation of historic beauty.
The staff guides you to your seat in a way that welcomes you and makes you feel special.
The majestic beauty surrounds you as you sit in comfortable seats.
The shows are always Spectacular

Boardwalk fries were very good. Went back next day for a large. Large is big enough to share. We got the overstuffed Virginia ham sub, it was delicious. Tried the seafood platter. Crab cake was mostly crab meat but I didn't like it fried. I will try baked next time. Everything was fresh and made to order. Ladies were very sweet and patience as though it was our first time. Great bite to eat!
The best salads in town! And they have vegan/vegetarian options to suite everyone’s needs. Great service with friendly staff. My coworker and I drive across town weekly for the salads and fries!!!!
Great experience! Excellent food and food service. Highly recommend the traditional gyro! Very friendly staff and they are all very family oriented. Love coming here

I wish they would open a sit down restaurant. Their food is ssssooooo good!! I’ve never had a bad experience in all the years I’ve been going. The gyros are melt in you mouth delicious 😋. I recommend them to everyone I meet. They have a big selection if you prefer something other than Greek food they probably have that too.

The funnel cake fries are delicious. The most important thing to me at any restuarant is the customer service. I'm always greeted at the window with a smile. I love everyone's personality. Thank you for the great food and service.
One of the best Peruvian food places in Western Maryland. The chicken is juicy and they provide at least 2 sides for meals. I recommend checking this place out.
Very good food.. Not sure many people are aware of just how great.. Nice quiet place to sit and get to know someone...

Overall a nice place to eat. The chicken is amazing and the ceviche is good. My mixed veggies were over cooked and mushy and very bland. The sauce cups are a little on the small side, but you get 8 with a whole chicken meal. The seating area is small but decent. They had tv’s on the wall to keep you entertained. Maybe I just caught my meal at the wrong time? I went for an early dinner, so perhaps the veggies were a left over from the lunch rush??
The prices are high but fair for the food you get. 
There are a few other Peruvian places around that I find to have better meals. That being said, the service was fast and I was satisfied with my food.
Amazing food decent atmosphere. Can be a bit longer wait than you might want if you're in a hurry. Pricing is a bit steep.

Horrible service.  The young girl at the register kept talking and playing videos on her phone instead of preparing the food I ordered.  I was the only person in the restaurant and it took over 20 minutes to make yucca (which she overcooked) one whole chicken and rice.  To make matters worse when my food was done it sat there while she was talking on the phone.  It wasn't until I said something that another lady came from the back and got it all ready.  No one even apologized.  Don't put children as the face of your restaurant!

Everything was excellent! Food came out in a timely manner. Everything tasted great. The employees were all very friendly. Would definitely recommend this restaurant to others. Restaurant definitely lives up to its name because the chicken is very flavorful!

Hands down the best chicken place ever!!! I love the chicken and the crab soup is to die for. Everyone here is very friendly! The owner of the restaurant is so awesome, always available, and super friendly and chatty with his customers, which I think is very important. This place will have my business for years to come.

I've been enjoying food from this location for over a year. 90% of the time it is take out. The favorite to-go dinner is the whole chicken and sides. The charbroiled chicken never disappoints. Perfectly cooked and seasoned with that summer char-grilled taste. While they offer many types of sides, I appreciate the fried rice (the texture is never mushy or over done with salt or oils) and the grilled veggies (always cooked from fresh produce and cooked with some tooth left in them.) If you eat in, the platters portions are very generous. Enchiladas are around $12/plate but you get three meat filled tortillas that have the perfect balance of sauce and cheese with a side of fresh salsa, sour cream, beans and fried rice. You also have plenty of bright flavored, freshly made condiment sides to make these dishes stand out. Try the jalapeno cream sauce over the fried rice and veggies. Spicy, but not enough to keep you from finishing your meal. And the owners and staff are always making something new to try. The service is polite and you are always greeted with an authentic smile. If your are unsure of what to try, ask for a suggestion! (Additionally, the chicken, veggies and rice are dairy free. Our son has a dairy allergy and has no reactions).
The best Peruvian Chicken around. Great prices and portions. Super clean, and their yellow sauce is out of this world.

Great food! I ordered the rotisserie chicken burrito. The chicken was AMAZING!!!! Super nice employees and clean facility. Burrito was huge so had to take half of it home. I would definitely go back and recommend to anyone :)
Great little bar. Popped in there late on out first night in Barcelona mid February. Nice relaxed atmosphere, & the drinks well priced. Would go again.
very well located in gracia, super friendly stuff, delicious tapas and good drinks :) We'll be back!

Had 6 days in Barcelona and visited this bar 4 times , both during the day and in the evening. Tapas was good . Very popular insomuch as we queued for a table on 3 occasions. I don't do that very often as there are plenty of bars. This bar is in a plaza so you have plenty of people to watch. Really enjoyed it.
Good service, lovely location to sit outside. Food and sangria was nice especially the goat cheese salad!
Amazing! Food and staff

First timer, FANTASTIC PLACE! From the outside it doesn't look impressive but once I walked in, I knew this place was something special. The service was terrific. But the food was definitely the star. I tried the BBQ Trip just to get a sample of as many items I could. I couldn't pick my favorite, it was all amazing. The next time I'm in the area, I will absolutely be back.

Brisket was dry as shoe leather, ribs were about the same.  The best parts were the sides and our waitress.  Shouldn’t have to drown my meat in sauce to eat it. Good BBQ should be able to stand alone. Just disappointing that they couldn’t deliver on their namesake.  

Definitely tasted like they smoked the meats, put them in a metal pan, wrapped it in Saran Wrap, only to stick it in a warmer to steam for hours before service.

Stopped in for a to-go lunch order on a Thursday. Not too busy, but certainly not dead. All of the staff I talked to were super friendly. I ordered the cream of crab soup, the brisket and a quarter rack of ribs. For sides I got the Mac & cheese and the veggie of the day (green beans sautéed in an Old Bay butter). 
The soup was delicious and FULL of crab meat- the best I've had in this area. The brisket was delicious, if slightly on the fatty side. The flavor was great, even without BBQ sauce- just enough smokey flavor to be good, but not so much that it's overpowering (I've got a picky eater at home who hates smoke flavor, and he would have still enjoyed this). I ordered the smaller portion, and it came with about 4 good sized slices, and they were tender enough that I used a spoon to cut them. The ribs were cooked well- the meat came off the bone easily and had a nice crust, though they weren't quite as flavorful as the brisket. The Mac & cheese was good, definitely made in-house (unlike a lot of other restaurants), and the green beans were fresh, though a little bland. 
All in all, it was a very good lunch and I'll definitely be back, especially for the crab soup and the brisket!

Love this place and they make the best collards north of Mississippi. Huge onion rings. Delicious BBQ. Fabulous service. The duck tacos were spectacular. And they even make an excellent Moscow Mule. Can't wait to go back.
Awesome experience.  Great waitstaff. Awesome bbq platter with different meats with each one having a unique flavor.  The wings were spicy and delicious too.

This place is closing tomorrow (4/27). There is literally nothing for either of us to gain or lose from this review. But... I have to say my experience here was incredible.

The service was fast and super friendly, and the food was some of the best I’ve eaten. Ever. I had an incredible curried vegetable stew, with subtle hints of coconut and cream. Tender chicken and attractive garnish. Soda refills were frequent from the extremely polite wait team.

Despite it being their literal last supper in business, it was obvious the owners and employees put effort and care into their customers’ experiences. I wish the owners only the best in their future endeavors. My single regret is that I won’t be able to eat here again.

Thank you all very much and best luck!
The best red curry I found in this area in YEARS. Very yummy. Generous portion. The service was great. And the aesthetic is clean and nice.
The curry that my wife and I ordered were very good and not too spicy (lvl2 spice). The service was quick and friendly. We will be coming back again. They also have a nice selection of import beers.

First time I went I was impressed by how nice and super friendly the server was. Now to the food, I believe the food was great o love Thai food and this place didn’t disappoint me one bit. Will be coming back to try more delicious food!
One of my favorite little holes in the walls.  I love the thai iced tea and rice here.  Great family restaurant.
Awesome Pho and even better price. Other dishes are good too. The place can use some improvement on the furniture. Friendly staff

Pho D'lite is Pho Delicious! We've been coming here for a while and the service has always been great. The food is super fresh, and comes out super fast. Today I tried the fried chicken and usually I just go for the Pho but OMG there are finger-licking good. Definitely would recommend this restaurant to anyone looking for a good meal.
I love this place, the $5 Pho and $1 Ice tea price during happy hour is awesome! Will definitely come back soon.
The food was absolutely horrible. Ordered $50 worth of food and could not eat it. This was my first time buying food there and i will absolutely not be going back.
The Pho is great and the prices are very affordable. No complaints here.

We went this past Saturday night for the first time can I say AMAZING FOOD! Can't wait to return. We had fabulous drinks, sampled three appetizers and four different dinners. Everyone loved it. Wonderful waitress couldn't be more pleasant. KUDOS!!!

This is one of my favorites for good quality food at a reasonable price. Not sure if they still serve it because their menu is seasonal but if you have the chance the land and sea burger is a great choice. First time I had ever heard of a crab cake on a burger and it was awesome! Erik's crab cakes are also another good option almost no filler and when they have it the French Dip is another good choice. Basically everything I have ordered here even if it's something I typically wouldn't order has been really good.

We enjoyed our food at Rik's Cafe. My group really liked the wings. They also shared a buffalo chicken dip over corn bread that was a hit. Not too many vegetarian options but the winter root vegetable salad was pretty nice. The root vegetables we're a bit tough but overall the salad was good. Service was efficient but not overly friendly. I would visit again if in the area, for sure.

Great place to visit in Hagerstown. Food is excellent and presented well. Been here on many occasions. Never disappointed. The sweet potatoes fries are the best I've ever had and when combined with the apple butter dipping sauce takes them to another level. Rik's is highly recommend in my book.

Whether stopping in for a quick beer or going for a full dine-out, Rik's is the right place. There are always good brews on draft and the food is outstanding. They come up with the most interesting lunch and dinner specials I have seen anywhere. The menu has a good selection, but is a little seafood-heavy. My only request is to add a couple more really good non-seafood selections to the menu. Love it and will return regularly.

I never had Indian Cuisine before. I order the chicken tikka and it was delicious. The place has a nice decor and my server was very nice and polite. If you like Indian cuisine or if you never had it give this place a try.

this best test best services and this most important test like India go this pleas and trying go go go!!!!
better then new Jersey city rasoi taste

Not Only a classy Decor, the food was the best I have had since moving to Hagerstown!, Im a Regular to Indian food, and this place left the other places in Hagerstown Standing !!!! Hands Down, you have to Eat here....

Joy

Fredrick Md
Friendly staff and excellent excellent food.
Closed out of business

If you are not gluten free, They have an amazing beer selection. 
Next part is a gluten free /gluten allergy review.
Food was not too bad was hoping for more out of the gluten free selection because everything is made in house and because they offer gluten free pizza and buns but shared fryers so couldn't have anything fried.

Grilled chicken wrap was awesome. My wife had the shrimp Caesar salad and said it was the best she ever had. Service was friendly and attentive. Nice open spaces, prices were reasonable. We're sad we don't live closer, we were really impressed.

Good food. Prices a little high, but not terrible.. Went early in the day so things seemed to be a bit slow... waited quite a while for the waitress and food etc.. but it wasn't too terrible. I'd try it again.
Really hit or miss. The servers and bar tenders are great. But some menu items are just kinda funky and don’t come out at well as they might plan.

A good place to grab a bite in town. Good beer selection, nice staff, and good food. Good prices for what your get. Doesn't stay open late because not much happens downtown Hagerstown these days. The bite sized shrimp appetizer is a really good deal, the crab wontons are amazing... The chef, Jay, truly cares. Not a cookie cutter place.

Was excited to try this place. Unfortunately it wasn't good. Went for the brunch on Sunday. Everything was cold. Prime rib was cold and looked like it had been sitting there all morning. The pork chops looked so good but they were dry and over cooked the sauce was vinegary tasting. For the price of the meal would think they would have good food. I could have gotten a better meal at Denny's and way cheaper. Quality wasn't any better. Service was slow and not very friendly. Will not return.

Won't be going back.  We went for brunch on Sunday and stood at the entrance for 10 minutes being ignored (wasn't very busy), when I finally asked if we seat ourselves or wait to be seated.  Server said someone would be with us and we ended waiting a while longer then finally the server came and just told us to sit by the fireplace.  We weren't aware it was only buffet and no menu.  The buffet was below par, frankly golden corral is better and a fraction of the cost.  Iceberg lettuce was not fresh, pork chops were so over cooked and dry almost like it was from a wedding the night before and just reheated. No one was at the egg making station or whatever it was, so I don't really know what was going on.  Prime rib was tough and cold and no horseradish.  Our server dropped off our drinks and that's all we saw of her.  Never got a refill on my coffee and drank all my water and had to resort to eating all of my ice bc apparently we were invisible and no one waited on us, at all.  The fireplace was nice and that's about it.  Over $18 for mediocre buffet and bad service not worth it. Go somewhere else!
Staff awesome. Saw the evening specials asked if I could order it. Yes. Warning the shrimp is heavily dosed with old bay. Otherwise a great experience.
Amazing selection of food for everyone to enjoy. The food inset never disappoints. The salad bar is also a plus. Excellent wine selection as well!
Stuffed shrimp were yummy... price was a little high and didn't know ahead it was a limited menu, but still a great meal! (and AWESOME service!)

Grossly overpriced, for the sole purpose of making those who can afford it feel good about themselves. For the rest of us, including those of us who unpretentiously enjoy the finer things in life, we are better off going elsewhere or just staying at home. (I must admit, this is based on only one visit.  But so be it.)
Great upscale service and food. It use to have a more sophisticated menu but still has an edge over most restaurants in the area
One of Hagerstown best.  Everything is done with elegance and style.  The food was prepare and cooked to perfection.  I loved my experiences each time I have gone.
The best restaurant to date I have found in Hagerstown. Food was excellent, staff were professional and polite and a good local beer list.
Worth the hour drive!!! Will be taking my wife there to celebrate our anniversary on Valentine's Day!!! Great food, service and wine selection!

Never again!!

Delivery took more than 2 hours.
The "groentenmix" suppose to be tempura vegetables, but contained prawn tempura (my wife is allergic to it) and there was a hair in the Yaki Udong Tori Teriyaki.....

All in all a real disappointment.
Super lekkere sushi, zowel om af te halen of om thuis te laten bezorgen. Regelmatig wat besteld altijd goed. Ze zijn snel!

Wij bestellen, of halen altijd af bij sakura als we thuis sushi gaan eten. Elke keer opnieuw weer top service. Sushi smaakt ons elke keer weer voortreffelijk en altijd z'n 45 min bezorgtijd. Zelfs vandaag op 2e kerstdag, wanneer er iets mis ging met onze bestelling, kregen we netjes een nieuw product. (Terwijl dit niet nodig was!) Het is dat ik nooit cash in huis heb, anders had ik zeker wat fooi als bedankje erbij gedaan! (Sorry daarvoor 🙈) Tot de volgende bestelling :)
Goede sushi kwaliteit. Stond op tijd klaar. Minpunt dat een blikje drinken niet was meegeleverd.
De beste sushi van Apeldoorn en heel veel keus in wat je wilt eten. Komen wel altijd later bezorgen dan je besteld en dat is wel teleurstellend. Maar heerlijk!

I was there recently and ordered Shrimp  salad  on a roll.  I ordered it to go.  They were fast  and friendly and the fries were perfect.
I couldn't give them 5 stars because of Dutches Daughter.  Once more because I love, LOVE their shrimp salad, it made Schula's seem a little  bland.  
However, if you haven't had Dutches then you should love Schula's.   They were jumbo shrimp and plenty of them for a good price.

I was really excited to come here with my family while heading down south. Unfortunately we were very disappointed. My mother and sister had steamed seafood platters and they were very dry, with no flavor. I had the shrimp and scallop scampi but it felt like they just melted butter and put parsley on top. The soda also tasted weird. It was flat and the soda didn't seem to have the right proportions of soda water and syrup. The reason this place was good was because of our server Kathleen. She was very sweet and beyond attentive. She made sure to fix any issues my family and I had. The only reason I gave this place 2 stars was because of how great Kathleen was.

Okay, I'm a seafood lover as it is, so that already makes this bias, but I have a special needs toddler, but I still wanted to celebrate a special occasion with another family member, and the waiter at our table was AMAZING with my son!!! The other waitress were not as amazing, at all as they would not let my son and I walk past them even though they were not carrying food, just expected us to change course (let alone the fact he's a toddler, but especially not as easy when dealing with special needs) But our waiter completely made up for their rudeness!!! He was kind, and fun, and genuine. Oh and the food was really good! We ordered a ton of food and it was all cooked perfectly! So thank you to the chef, and thank you to our waiter for a great dinning experience!

Schula's is a busy restaurant that was surprisingly not very noisy inside.  Reservations are a must because they book up and you will be unable to get a seat during peak hours.  My impression of the staff is that they are rather cordial, again a surprise.  So maybe not your typical louder, friendly, rowdy bar and grill type place, which I am not saying is good or bad, just different.  The food is good, but the unanimous consensus at my table is that the portion sizes could be bigger, especially for the price.   I can imagine those with heartier appetites leave feeling still a bit hungry.

This restaurant was recommended to me by the hotel front desk.  I checked it out online and I was excited to eat some fried oysters.  The food was very good and fairly priced...Service was very good.  The reason for 1 star?  I had the fried oysters which were excellent, however 7 hours later (2:30 A.M.), I was awakened to nausea, vomiting and well, I won't mention what else here.  I was very sick the entire next day which included a trip to Urgent Care where I was tested for the flu and ruled out.  Since the oysters, fries and coleslaw were the only meal I had eaten since pizza for lunch that day , I have to think the oysters were bad.  Obviously, the restaurant can't be held accountable for the seafood they receive, I suffered physically and financially for eating there.
